						<div class="postbody">Take a cue from the leading experts on preventing piracy, and mail NES consoles sealed in a steel box with only the buttons and outs exposed.  Place in the beta cart a self-destruct mechanism that will destroy the rom chips should they somehow get in.  Like a small glass tube of acid that will break when the shell is split open.  Acid can corrode silicon wafers, right?</div>

